FBIS4-61794 "drsov090_v_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-090 Daily Report 9 May 1994 Lithuania Reaction to Grachev Statement on Suspending Troop Pullout Reaction to Grachev Statement on Suspending Troop Pullout Statement Shows `Disrespect' for Estonia LD0905150894 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network in Lithuanian 1400 GMT 9 May 94 LD0905150894 Vilnius Radio Vilnius Network Lithuanian BFN [Text] We have received a statement made by the Lithuanian Ministry of Foreign Affairs concerning Russia's threats. It indicates that a statement made by Pavel Grachev and Russia's policy in general on the negotiations with Estonia show disrespect toward the partner in negotiations and for international law as well as for the processes and documents of all Europe's members and participants, of which Russia itself is one [sentence as heard]. Such statements made by high-ranking Russian officials increase tension in the region and threaten the security of the Baltic countries, the statement by the Lithuanian Ministry of Foreign Affairs reads.
